data.content:
**Yes, it works.** You can `stackalloc` both `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>` without issues. On this 64-bit system each element is 8 bytes. The syntax is straightforward:

```csharp
Span<nint>  signed   = stackalloc nint[4];
Span<nuint> unsigned = stackalloc nuint[4];
```

This has been supported since C# 9 / .NET 5, when `nint`/`nuint` were introduced as first-class types (aliases for `System.IntPtr` / `System.UIntPtr`).
